      private String getReturnDefaultValue(Class<?> token)

      void produce ""

      constructable types produce "null"

      boolean produce "false"

      other primitive types produce zero

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args) throws ImplerException
      Static entry-point

      There should be two or three arguments. All arguments have to be defined (not null). When got two arguments run Impler.implement(Class, Path) When got three arguments and first equals -jar run JarImpler.implementJar(Class, Path)

      Parameters:
      args - array with given arguments.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - when incorrect args or it throws implementJar(Class, Path) or implement(Class, Path)

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Create .jar file, which contains compiled implemented class Method takes type token and path to results .jar file. File will be compiled by system java compiler. If something went wrong, ImplerException will throw.
      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - interface type token.
      jarFile - path to resulting .jar file
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if something IOException occurred(in creating/removing temporary directory or in creating/writing .jar file if compilation was failed
